Server
    Create a socket on which server will listen to the upcoming clients.
    Create a structure which will store IP address and port number on which server will listen.
    Bind both the socket and port number.
    Start listening.
    Accept the incoming client connection request and creates a new socket for conversation between server and that specific client.
    Close the sockets


Client
    Create a socket. 
    Create a structure which will store IP address (can be different from server) and port number (same as of server).
    Send the connection request
    If accepted, send/receive the message
    Close the socket